      • radiusRecurse

        public void radiusRecurse​(double r,
                          KDNode<T> curr,
                          double[] target,
                          MultiTreeMap<Double,​KDPoint> nearPoints,
                          int excludeID)
        Recursive method to determine the points within a given radius of a target.
        Parameters:
        r - radius around the target where nodes must be found
        curr - current node which is being examined
        target - target point which will act as the origin
        nearPoints - data structures which will contain all the values within r radius of the target
        excludeID - the id of any value which you don't want to be included map of near points. -1 should be passed in to indicate that no points should be excluded.

        public String toString()
        toString method for the k-d tree.
        Overrides:
        toString in class Object
        Returns:
        returns a string containing all the nodes in the form x : y [coords] where x is the depth of the node and y is its position along the tree at that depth, assuming the tree is complete.
